The paper discusses the learning mechanism of a robot to estimate dialogue acts through human-robot interaction, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of scaffolding, which is a technique used in educational psychology and human-computer interaction, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of a robot, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning to estimate dialogue acts, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
